cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with data quality measurement, which is a fundamental problem in database management. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also employs association rule mining, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The use of genetic algorithms for rule generation and feature selection suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses interestingness of the generated rules, which is a common topic in information retrieval, making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
